name: Sirel Mouchantaf
short_description:
Sirel Mouchantaf is an engineering professional working in Fredericksburg, VA with over twenty years of experience in heavy civil and rail projects. He graduated with a Bachelor’s Degree in Civil Engineering and a Master’s Degree in Engineering Management (MSEM) from Syracuse University. The MSEM program helps working engineers and scientists become better managers as well as  become prepared for increased responsibilities in management. The degree program provided Sirel with knowledge in management theory and practices, statistics, quality control, finance, economics, information/data management, and legal issues. In his spare time, Sirel enjoys spending time with his family and working on home improvement projects. Sirel is also a huge soccer fan and continues to be active in the sport with multiple leagues in the DC, Virginia and Maryland areas.
